news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit increases by 69.27% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Shriram Properties' consolidated total income from operations stood at Rs 222.01 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 70.62 per cent from Rs 130.12 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: NBCC's net profit dips 17.40% in Q3 FY23
news.para: NBCC's consolidated total income from operations stood at Rs 2,191.24 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 7.27 per cent from Rs 2,042.79 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Poddar Housing & Development posts net loss of Rs 9.39 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: The board of directors of Poddar Housing & Development approved and recommended the sale/disposal off their project 'Poddar Riveria' situated at Mahral, Kalyan to Runwal Developers by way of slump sale.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net profit of Rs 9.05 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Ashiana Housing's consolidated total income stood at Rs 135.31 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 110.80 per cent from Rs 64.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit up 75% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 2,347.50 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 74.22 per cent from Rs 1,347.40 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: DPIIT considering quality control norms for certain building materials
news.para: ​In this regard, the department has sought industry comments on draft quality control orders (QCOs) for concrete, asbestos, gypsum and ceramic-based materials industry.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation cracks whip on illegal change of building occupancy
news.para: Corporation secretary Binu Francis issued a circular citing complaints regarding the revenue wing changing the occupancy without the consent of the engineering wing.

news.title: Vipul's net loss widens to Rs 13.91 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Vipul's consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 8.60 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 89.01 per cent from Rs 78.28 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Will use property tax data, electricity bill to increase GST base: CBIC Chairman
news.para: The CBIC Chairman said the board's strategy regarding GST is that collecting revenue is its target, along with that it is also necessary to increase the tax base.

news.title: Dust pollution: Citizens urge BMC to monitor construction in Mumbai
news.para: Given that each of the 24 BMC wards in Mumbai has a strength of 250-300 employees, and in addition, a complement of temporary workers, it may be time for them to fan out and track big projects in their respective jurisdictions, say experts.

news.title: Ludhiana: Builders say e-portal for NOCs delaying deals, ask PUDA official to intervene
news.para: ​​A delegation of Punjab Colonisers and Property Dealers Association (PCPDA) on Monday met the chief administrator of Punjab Urban Development Authority (PUDA), which is the nodal agency for the portal, to discuss these issues.

news.title: Gurugram civic body examines information on 86,000 more properties
news.para: The data of over 1.5 lakh properties could not be collected as 92,065 were vacant plots and 60,730 owners denied to share information with surveyors.

news.title: Fire safety over cost: India's path to sustainable growth
news.para: Strict adherence to building codes and use of fire-retardant material must to safeguard lives

news.title: Registration of property in Chennai records a spike
news.para: Between April 2022 and January 2023, the city has registered a 40% spike in number of property registered, while the state registered a 30% hike compared to the same period in the previous fiscal.

news.title: Telangana high court junks ED petition on Karvy Realty
news.para: ED counsel argued that PMLA does not allow any such time for the accused as the adjudicating authority is under an obligation to pronounce a decision within 180 days on the attachments made by the ED authorities.
